  "text": "Angiotensin II receptor blockers are favoured by some clinicians. Although there is a good theoretical rationale for their use, the evidence base is weak (only one open-label randomised clinical trial [CITATION_1] ). Angiotensin converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitors are seldom used for RP: the minimal evidence base examining their use is conflicting, and the largest study which was of quinapril (210 patients with either limited cutaneous SSc or with SSc-specific autoantibodies) reported no benefit in terms of either RP attacks or digital ulcers [CITATION_2] .",
