      "span_text": "Angiotensin converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitors are seldom used for RP: the minimal evidence base examining their use is conflicting, and the largest study which was of quinapril (210 patients with either limited cutaneous SSc or with SSc-specific autoantibodies) reported no benefit in terms of either RP attacks or digital ulcers"
